The principles of the Estonian judicial system and the general bases of the court administration. Establishment of guardianship and grounds for court procedures (minor, adult,) guardian, the extent of guardianship, functions of local government in establishing guardianship. General organisation of the state victim support, content and bases of provision of victim support service. Content and grounds for the application of the National Family Mediation Service.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide the student with general knowledge of the basics of court administration, which would allow them to assist clients in the preparation of documents necessary for the protection of their rights (court and other institutions).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows the principles and values of the Estonian judicial system and the general foundations of the judicial organisation; 2) knows general principles of guardianship, grounds for establishing guardianship and court procedures, functions of local government in establishing guardianship; 3) knows general bases for the organisation of state victim support and assistance provided in terms of the Victim Support Act; 4) knows the objectives of the National Family Mediation Service and the bases for the organisation of conciliation procedures.
